According to the Drude model of free electrons in metals:

\[
\sigma = \frac{1}{\rho} = \frac{n e^{2} \tau}{m}
\]

Thus,

\[
\tau = \frac{1}{\rho} \cdot \frac{m}{n e^{2}}
\]

At 295 K:

\[
\begin{aligned}
