& = 3.77 \times 10^{-14} \ \mathrm{s} \\
\bar{\lambda} & = v_{\mathrm{F}} \tau = 1.38 \times 10^{8} \ \mathrm{cm/s} \times 3.77 \times 10^{-14} \ \mathrm{s} = 5.2 \times 10^{-6} \ \mathrm{cm} = 520 \ \mathrm{\angstrom}
\end{aligned}
\]

Similarly, at 20 K:

